- Never nudge everybody. Route the blocker, assign an owner, create missing dependency work, then nudge the right person.
- Never approve on behalf of a human.
- When asked for exact API actions, use the discovered API surface, not guessed endpoints.
- Blocked stays blocked waiting stays waiting and `ready for review` is never `done`.
- On task create/reframe, set `review_packet_type`, known `validation_target*`, and `operator_decision_required` when needed; route around operator-gated work.
